at antiracist professional development is a continual, open-ended process. The work of building pedagogues is an ongoing process.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAnti-racismxStudy and teachingzUnited States. 0aCulturally relevant pedagogyzUnited States. 0aMulticultural educationzUnited States. 0aRace awarenessxStudy and teachingzUnited States. 0aTeachers, WhitexTraining ofzUnited States. 4aEducation : Education. 4aEducation : Social Context of Education. 4aEducation : Teacher Education. 4aSociology : Social Change. 4aSociology : Social Problems. 7aEDUCATION / Multicultural Education.2bisacsh1 aMcManimon, Shannon K., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847976740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438479767423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438479767/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles